{"build_type":"library","module_name":"grab-stack-chunk","package_name":"grab-stack-chunk","description":"Segregated fan-out stack allocator (fix: block-stack pool overlap). Hands an 8MiB worker stack chunk from the DEDICATED page-aligned stack segment carved by install-fixed-arena, keeping stack addresses physically disjoint from arena blocks/chunks in the main pool. Reclaim is CONTEXT-routed through a dedicated stack ring (ring3 = slab+24+3*65560), never the by-size main rings, so an 8MiB arena-grow chunk can never be handed as a stack (or vice versa). Tries ring3 reuse; else bumps the stack segment cursor at pool_base[105] bounded by pool_base[106]. Returns chunk+16 with chunk[0]=needed+16, matching grab-released-or-fresh-arena-chunk so recycle routes it back by size(==8MiB+16). GUARD PAGE: allocates extra 4KB PROT_NONE page at the bottom of each fresh bump-allocated chunk. Stack overflow into the guard produces a loud SIGSEGV instead of silent neighbour corruption. Guard is page-aligned via shift-rounding, adding up to 4095 bytes of alignment padding per chunk. Reused chunks from the reclaim ring keep their existing layout (no retroactive guard).","function_definitions":{"grab-stack-chunk":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"needed_bytes","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"deqmagic","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":3520188881},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"two","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":2},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"sixteen","variable_type":"